author: Trevor Smith
title: Nav "Myself" Video
text:
Posted by Trevor Smith  59pm Subscribe to HNHH TV NAV shares a psychedelic video for his catchy party record "Myself." 
"Myself" is a pretty good representation of NAV as an artist. A slightly brighter, simpler, more light-hearted take on The Weeknd 's drug-fuelled late-night tales ("When I'm sober I just don't like who I am/Pour me up a 4 and I'll feel like myself again" is a strikingly similar sentiment to "when I'm fucked up/that's the real me," tey it's delivered in a decidedly more playful cadence.This is the formula much of the rapper and singer's self-titled debut follows, and the video for "Myself" hammers home the themes found throughout. Trippy, mirroring filters and purpley hues set the party-life atmosphere right, and befire you know it, pills are falling from the sky in a torrential downpour. Stream NAV's self-titled album here and look out for his upcoming collaborative project with Metro Boomin . NAV shares a psychedelic video for his catchy party record "Myself."
